'''convection'''

# the process of [[conveying]] something
#{{physics}} the [[transmission]] of [[heat]] in a [[fluid]] by the [[circulation]] of [[current]]s
#(''meteorology'') the vertical movement of heat and moisture, especially by updrafts and downdrafts in an [[unstable]] air mass. The terms convection and [[thunderstorm]] are often used [[interchangeably]], although [[thunderstorm]]s are only one form of convection. Towering [[cumulus]] clouds are visible forms of convection.